1. What is blogging? - Ask Bruce Question of the week   
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
 
Blogging is a way of collecting links to pages you visit often and making comments about them that other people can see. They're great because they have really personal reviews of websites. 

They're also really easy to make so you can have one even if you aren't very technical, so take a look at Ask Bruce.

 http://www.bbc.co.uk/webwise/askbruce/articles/browse/blogging_1.shtml

2. Portable player unlocks net radio
 --------------------------------------------

An innovative radio that lets you listen to internet stations anywhere in the home has been showcased at the world's largest consumer technology event in Las Vegas. A radio that connects to a computer wirelessly, providing access to any music on the PC or to thousands of internet radio stations. 

So to find out more go to BBCi news to read the full article.

http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/2652239.stm

3. Bill Thompson - Get a move on BT
------------------------------------------------

It’s really great that BT wants us all to get broadband. The telecoms giant is spending a million pounds a day on TV adverts over the coming week, and will follow that up with a £23 million campaign to push its new ‘no-frills’ broadband service.

Read the Bill Thompson column at the WebWise site.

http://www.bbc.co.uk/webwise/column/

4. Are you new to the Internet? - Becoming WebWise 
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Why not try the Becoming WebWise course - or recommend it to your friends.  Becoming WebWise is an easy to use step-by-step online course that will help make you a confident internet user.

Make the first step today, go online and explore Becoming WebWise

http://www.bbc.co.uk/becomingwebwise

5. Great Shortcut tips - Tip of the Week
--------------------------------------------------

Fed up of using the menus and the mouse to select text and cut or copy and paste it.  Why not try the shortcut keys on your keyboard! Control + c = copy, Control + v = paste, Control + x = paste, shift end = selects a line.

Practise them today and see how easy it!

 
6.Starship has launched
-------------------------------

Starship is the BBC's brand new service to support 6-7 year old children with English and Maths skills in Year 2.  The site, accompanying TV programmes, materials and radio broadcasts have all been created with the aim of making learning fun as they prepare for their National Tests at the end of Key Stage 1.

Take a look at the Starship site today and put the fun back into learning.

http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/starship/


